fields.description: We can evaluate to see if you have acne and start or refill treatment to reduce blemishes and prevent future acne from occurring.

questions.title: How did you hear about DearBrightly?

children.title: Tell us more about how you heard about DearBrightly.

choices.hint: Topical retinoid safety is not fully established in pregnant and breastfeeding women.
choices.label: Breastfeeding

choices.label: Pregnant

questions.description: Certain conditions can complicate diagnosis, increase risks, or change the recommended treatments so it is critical the medical provider knows everything going on with your health.

questions.title: How would you characterize your skin?

choices.label: Combination (oily skin along the T-zone, dryer skin around the cheeks, some blackheads, enlarged pores around the T-Zone)
Dry (dull complexion, flaky skin, fine pores)
Normal (fine pores, smooth texture, no blemishes)
Oily (enlarged pores, shiny complexion, blackheads, whiteheads, acne, blemishes)
Sensitive (prone to itching and irritation; symptoms include redness, dryness, scaling, bumps)

questions.title: What kind of climate do you live in?
Do you have any concerns with your skin?

children.title: Tell us more about your skin concerns.

questions.title: Do you currently take any medicines, herbals, or supplements?

choices.label: No, not taking any medicines, supplements, herbals, or other prescriptions

children.title: What medicines, herbals, or supplements do you take?

questions.description: Please include any over-the-counter and prescription medicines you finished recently, including topical medicines and any injections, vitamins, or herbal remedies.

questions.title: Do you have any allergies or reactions to medication?

choices.label: No, don't have any allergies or medication reactions

children.title: What allergies or reactions to medication do you have?

questions.description: Please include all allergies and/or minor and major reactions to medicines.

questions.title: Have you ever used or are currently using any prescription topicals for acne or skin aging?

children.title: Please name the prescription topical(s) along with formulation strength (e.g., 0.025%, 0.05%, 0.1%), vehicle (e.g., cream, gel, foam), and timeframe (e.g., currently using, used 4 years ago for 3 months, etc).
Did the prescription topical cause dryness, irritation, oiliness, etc.? If so, describe.

questions.description: For example, Retin A (Tretinoin), Differin (Adapalene), or Tazorac (Tazarotene).

questions.title: Are you currently using over-the-counter topicals in your skincare regimen?

children.title: Please list all the topicals in your skincare regimen.

questions.description: For example, Vitamin C serum, sunscreen, chemical peel, or benzoyl peroxide.

questions.title: Have you ever had any medical conditions?

choices.label: No, never had any of these

children.title: Please include even any minor or recent conditions or symptoms. The medical provider needs to know your full history to give you the best care.

questions.description: If you have any medical conditions not listed, please select "Other" and list them. Even if they are in the past, certain conditions can complicate diagnosis, increase risks, or change the recommended treatments so it is critical the medical provider knows your full history.

questions.title: Is there anything else about your skin the doctor should know?

children.title: What else would you like the doctor to know?
